    Fixed issue data gen bug and improved formatting to visualisation.
    
    The issue with the wrong validation split arguments mention in the last
    commit has been fixed. A preliminary training run of the model with the
    fixed testing/training splits has been completed with 5 epochs, a
    training dice coefficient of 0.78 and a testing of 0.87. These results
    indicate a longer more complete training run will produce good results.
    
    Improved formating of the data visualisation, removed usage of grispec
    and added titles, xlabels, and improved spacing on all plots.

    fix I will remove it.
    Complete a 10-15 epoch training run.

commit 6e1a2c463a4eeb2385f588fd506e5d3514ec1b9d
Author: d7a7 <douglas@atherton.co>
Date:   Mon Nov 1 10:57:17 2021 +1000

    Updated test visualisation and implemented test set testing.
    
    The functions for visualising the predicted masks compared to real masks
    were updated and integrated into the main function. The visualisation
    function now accurately shows two test images, their predicted masks and
    their ground truth masks.
    
    A function that avaluates the model on the entire test dataset was
    implemented and integrated into the main function. This function
    performs an evaluation on the entire 20% of all images that were
    reserved for testing. It achieved a 0.89 Dice Coefficient score.
    
    Due to these results, further refinement of the model, augmentation, and
    training process is not needed.
    
    Todo: Improve annotations on test visualisation output and look at why
    the data the model['accuracy'] is tracking seems to be not relevant.

    into data_loading.ipynb has been moved to a standalone model.py file

Author: yousifpatti <yousifpatti@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Oct 31 11:50:02 2021 +1000

    Fixed an issue with caused by removing numpy.zeros
    
    Remvoing numpy.zeors and replacing it with tf.zeros caused the issue of returning an Eager tensor object instead of an array and as such was throwing not assignable error. To fix I converted the tf.zeros object into an array after it was created in both driver.py for the priors and in model.py for the PixelCNN model.

commit cf6ef4e3f459fa37098c381efcec4b4722a0a903
Author: LABS\s4539629 <s>
Date:   Sat Oct 30 13:11:42 2021 +1000

    Major updates (see below)
    
    Model:
    - Tidy up F1 score function
    - Added Custom Callback placeholder in model outer class
    - Made num_classes and model feature map scale both init parameters when creating the outer class
    - Made model nodes accessible outside creation function
    - Removed hardcoded class nums in multiple places and repointed to init parameter (e.g. last model Conv layer)
    - Implemented Model saving function
    - Added docstrings
    
    Driver:
    - Added deterministic randomization for data split function to ensure subsequent testing does not overlap with data used for training originally
    - Functionized training datum pre-prep (e.g. standardization) as these are reused during model evaluation (predict) tasks as well
    - Added new function for evaluating a model. Used during training (against val data) and subsequently during the testing phase (against test data)
    - Tidy up of training loop. Now calls evaluation function (above) every x epochs (x set by user)
    - Added function to load a saved model and test it against the test dataset (evaluate F1 score). Optionally saves the predictions to file for 3D image browsing.
    - Added docstrings

Date:   Thu Oct 28 23:11:10 2021 +1000

    The model will now exceed a Dice Similarity Coefficient of 0.8! Removed Kernel Initializer and activation from each Conv2D to fix static loss and improve performance. Modified the dice loss function to give the correct result and added soft dice as a metric for the model. Modularised certain functions in driver.py to implement conditional operation. Added the ability to save and reuse a model that had previously been trained. Reduced condition where an early stopping would occur (4 to 3)

commit 0849282534d4ec9b73b8f2ffa528954defea65e1
Author: yousifpatti <yousifpatti@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Oct 27 00:40:24 2021 +1000

    Added the driver and model trainer
    
    This new file contains the driver of the models and trainer model used in a previous commit. Changes include adding adding each layer separately and adding a pre-vq_vae layer. The model is compiled in sequence just to view the summary but it is not used. The custom train_step would train all the layers on it's own and calculate the loss on each step. Finally, losses are printed and model training history is saved. Furthermore, I added training hyperparameters that help adjust the model layers and propagate change easier compared to pervious implementation where it was just numbers and not variables.

    Add helper function in the dataset.py to help load data to the pixelcnn
    model.
    1. train_codebook_generator() and validate_codebook_generator(), generators that load the processed data from dataset to the models in batches.
    2. process_data(), process the data before passing them to the model.
    In particular, it pass the original image to the vqvae encorder and map
    the ouput from the encoder to its closest latent embedding vector in the
    latent space.

commit a79f479aa40b586a8b1760bc4f89e631a0b82020
Author: Shravan Shivpuri <s.shivpuri@uqconnect.edu.au>
Date:   Sun Oct 24 22:44:43 2021 +1000

    Major fixes to Model and Driver (See detailed log below):
    
    Model now trains but is overfitting training data quite well. Need to implement weighted loss to improve.
    
    Model:
    1. Moved ReLU to AFTER BN layer as per research paper. Previously BN was scheduled after ReLU.
    2. Changes output Conv3D layer feature map count to match number of classes (6)
    3. Changed loss to Categorical Cross Entropy (Not binary)
    4. Added scale factor to feature map counts
    5. Minor updates to Dice (F1) score (still not coded - however removing tf function decorator gets rid of errors)
    6. Added placeholder for Weighted cross entropy loss
    
    Driver:
    1. MAJOR BUGFIX: Removed accidentally applying standardization to the LABELS which was killing learning.
    2. Converted labels to one-hot encoding required for multi-class classification learning
    3. Wrapped in a simple training loop

    Add dataset.py to handle image preprocessing before passing them to the model.
    It contains the following four methods:
    1. load_data(), load images from the dataset

       dataset, preprocesses them in the required format and pass them to
